article.headline: Auburn 86, Tennessee State 59
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Auburn got a near triple-double from forward Josh Dollard, who had 16 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists, on the way to beating Tennessee State 86-59 Tuesday night. The difference in the game was taking care of the basketball. Auburn (9-3) had 26 assists and 11 turnovers while TSU (4-5) had just eight assists and 21 turnovers. Auburn's two point guards, Quantez Robertson and Dwayne Reed, combined for eight assists and just one turnover. Tennessee State got 13 points from Ladarious Weaver and 15 points off the bench from Moraye Ivy. Auburn's Korvotney Barber was the game's leading scorer with 17 points while adding nine boards and five blocks in just 23 minutes. Frank Tolbert chipped in 12 points and Kelvin Lewis added 10. Quan Prowell, who was making his Auburn debut after transferring from Furman and serving an 11-game suspension, had six points and three rebounds but fouled out after playing nine minutes.
